import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='precipitation', data=data, label='Precipitation')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of precipitation over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Precipitation')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data['month'] = data['date'].dt.strftime('%b')

    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    sns.boxplot(x='month', y='temp_max', data=data, color='red', ax=ax)
    sns.boxplot(x='month', y='temp_min', data=data, color='blue', ax=ax)

    red_patch = plt.Line2D([], [], color='red', label='temp_max')
    blue_patch = plt.Line2D([], [], color='blue', label='temp_min')
    plt.legend(handles=[red_patch, blue_patch])

    plt.title('How does temperature vary throughout the year?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Month')
    plt.ylabel('Temperature')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.scatterplot(x='wind', y='temp_max', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the relationship between wind and temperature?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Wind')
    plt.ylabel('Max Temperature')
    plt.legend(title='Temperature', loc='upper right', labels=['Temperature'])
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    weather_counts = data['weather'].value_counts()
    sns.barplot(x=weather_counts.index, y=weather_counts.values)
    plt.xlabel('Weather Conditions')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the most common weather condition?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
